column1: Prompt column contains the exact prompt that the facilitator should read.
This is words, not symbols in order to be unambiguous. (e.g. write "multiply" instead of *, because * is ambiguous -- could be read as "times" or "multiply".)
Contains the correct answer that we expect. Actual correct answer could be any variation on this. Facilitator should use their judgement.
Record "c" for a correct answer and "w" for a wrong answer. (Participant 0 is an example.)
